\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\sl480\slmult1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang4105\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105\i0\b0 \tab Solar force is a cosmic energy existent only through reaction.  This energy is the driving force present in the galactic substances of space that causes their movement, and exists only because of their movement.  It is the basis for chain reaction of all 
substances in the earth plane.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang4105\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105\i0\b0 \tab The atom contains more controlled solar force than the total of the substance it composes.  A better explanation of this would be:  the smaller and more compact the system, the greater solar force activated.  The total substance puts out only a small port
ion of the solar force contained; whereas each individual atom activates the total of it's solar force.  This energy is directed to the nearest other atom present, thus activating it to do the same.  When this has been completed, and all the atoms are acti
vating each other in the substance, the force returns to begin again the cycle of reaction.  The substance itself is merely the container for the solar force, and is allowed only a certain amount to activate outside it's own system.  When atomic energy is 
disrupted, the solar force does not follow this pattern, and the energy leaves it's cycle of reaction to become the enrgy output of the total substance.  Unequipped to control such energy, the substance expells the force, causing what is termed as an \'93expl
osion\'94.  When the explosion takes place not all of the solar force is effective, as much is dissipated instantly on release by the abruptness in which it is thrown into chaos.  The amount utilized upon release depends on the density of the particles of the
 substance and the violence of the release.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang4105\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang4105\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang4105\loch\f0\fs24\lang4105 
