he other's balance that their presence (not their structure) is indestructible.  A plane is the one indestructible state in the universe.  All must continue forever, that is true, but all but the planes are subject to eventual complete change of state.  Th
e planes may change their structure within, change their holding conditions and limitations, but always they remain as planes.  This continuance is assured by a moving, surging power flowing on the pulsebeat of the universe. This is the nebulous strain.  T
he simplest description that I can give is that it is a current beyond that we know as magnetic, flowing through the universe in arc fashion, from which first state energy is created.  The nebulous strain is the one artery of the universe, stemming from th
e central point or the moment of creation.  It keeps the planes in harmony by drawing in certain energies and creating new ones when needed.  It was caused by the suction of the planes, and in turn, maintains their suction.  The strain does not exist in al
l planes, only in the ones in it's path, as it flings itself outward from the central point.  However, it's influence reaches to all points of the universe.  It is the guardian of all universal law.  A clear description of the nebulous strain is not found 
in any eathly vocabulary.  It is too vast, too close to the essence of God.}
