must be eliminated from it's galaxy lest it throw the galaxy as a whole into imbalance.  The great sensitivity of the universe detects that star's imbalance and the galaxy in which the star exists shifts it's left angle to an even sharper degree.  All mass
es that are balanced securely within the galaxy maintain their positions unharmed, but the star in imbalance is drawn by the nebulous strain, as it's position has been jarred, and therefore plunges toward the strain.  If the nebulous strain is not present 
on the plane that contains the star, the star is forced into a plane change.  Since it's balance is lost, however, it will not go through the natural limitations law to reach the nebulous strain.  It attempts to break through it's plane without creating th
e needed limitations or reaching the natural ones.  In it's attempt it is thrown back into itself and it's energy output becomes it's input.  This contradicts the solar force present, and the solar force, sensing the disturbance, leaves it's cycle to becom
e the output of the mass.  It is immediately thrown back into itself, causing an inner eruption of energy, thus changing it's state to first state energy on all planes recognizing it's existence.  (Note:  each individual mass of energy exists on only a cer
tain number of planes.  On other planes it does not exist.  On each plane that it does exist it is in a different state.  First state energy if the exception.)  When the star is in a total first state energy condition, it can easily escape from it's trappe
d exsitence and make a direct plane change into a plane in which flows the nebulous strain.  It then enters the strain as pure energy to be replenished, stored, and eventually released again in another state.  }
