iversal travel can pass onto a star wave by correlating the magnetic energy precisely with the magnetic energy of the star wave.  Also, it must obtain the same velocity and this must be accomplished in fixed space.  This pertains, of course, only to the ea
rth plane and similar planes.  On plance not containing similar holding conditions different actions would need to be achieved in order to be placed on the star wave.  Their patterns are vast, leaving many sections with waves either nonexistance or too wea
k to carry a ship or too violent.  A spaceship can use these star waves to a great extent in universal travel but must also rely on the ship's own magnetic waves when the star waves are not accessible.  }
