 both were traveling at the same speed (Note:  the speed being measured from earth), upon entering free space the smaller Comet A would appear much faster and cover more distance in the same amount of earth time than Comet B.  Each comet would contain it's
 own time factor upon entering free space, according to size and composition.  In reality, each comet would continue with equal velocity, only the time scale would differ.  }
