not subject to the physical world of matter and anti-matter.  If a physical system is altered, changed or reversed, it will not directly effect the time plane.  This statement may seem in contradiction to \'93The Principles of Space-time\'94.  There is no contra
diction.  Space is subject to time the same as is energy (on the earth plane in the form of matter and anti-matter), but space is also subject to energy.  The time factor of a comet traveling through free space would change it's scale in accordance with th
e change of state in it's physical presence.  The free space would be responding to the physicl presence of the comet, thus through the laws of time controlling the space, time is brought about relative to the comet in motion and to the change of it's phys
ical presence.  Therefore, time is not directly influeneced by the changing conditions of matter and anti-matter, space is the influenced factor and, as space is subject to the laws of time, it must respond in time frequencies to anything occupying it's sp
ace.  }
